lead_paragraph: CALIFORNIA Having won California as Bill Clinton's running mate in 1992 and 1996, Vice President Al Gore captured the state's 54 electoral votes yesterday. Senator Dianne Feinstein, a Democrat and former mayor of San Francisco, beat back a challenge from Representative Tom Campbell, a Republican from Silicon Valley.
abstract: California election roundup: Vice Pres Al Gore wins state; Sen Dianne Feinstein, Democrat, wins re-election over Rep Tom Campbell; voters reject ballot measure to offer school vouchers to students wishing to move from public to private schools (S)
